info.headline: Flood Warning issued April 13 at 8:29PM CDT until further notice by NWS GreenBay
info.description: ...Observed flooding changed to Minor severity for the following rivers in Michigan...Wisconsin... Brule River near Commonwealth affecting Forest, Dickinson, Florence and Iron Counties. ...FLOOD WARNING FOR SNOWMELT REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring. * WHERE...Brule River near Commonwealth. * WHEN...Until further notice. * IMPACTS...At 12.0 feet, Flooding is mainly confined to wooded lowland areas. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 7:30 PM CDT Thursday the stage was 12.4 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 7:30 PM CDT Thursday was 12.4 feet. - Forecast...No forecast is available for this location. - Flood stage is 12.0 feet. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 12.5 feet on 04/23/2019. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued Friday morning.
